wing and seeking out the motives of criminals, exploring the subtlest emotions driving them. It’s not to put ourselves in their shoes and sympathize, or even forgive them; it’s not to find some reasons to exculpate their crimes; it’s not to kneel down before the so-called \"complexity of human nature\"; nor to introspect social conflicts, much less to alienate ourselves into monsters.\n\nWe just want to have a fair trial – for ourselves and for those who still have hope for the world.\n\n(Source: NovelUpdates)', '#252525', '#333333', '#ffffff', '#ffffff', '#ffffff'),
